oc:kn_03b2831d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During Phase 1 data collection when gathering transcript materials" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify the earnings call transcript date matches the earnings release date (±1 day). If they don't match, you have the wrong transcript." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mismatched dates indicate you grabbed an old transcript from a prior quarter, leading to incorrect analysis" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_0c1573f6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — before any analysis begins" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before starting: (1) Write down today's date, (2) Search for '[Company] latest earnings results', (3) Verify release date is within 3 months, (4) Confirm transcript date matches release date." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The #1 mistake in earnings analysis is using outdated data; this 4-step check prevents that failure mode" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_0d5858bc a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the earnings update report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do NOT write an initiation-length report. Earnings updates are 8-12 pages with 1-3 summary tables only. Do not include full P&L, Cash Flow, or Balance Sheet." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Institutional clients already know the company from the initiation report and need fast, focused analysis of what changed" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2a9dde09 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Phase 5 quality check before delivering report to user" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before delivery: verify beat/miss quantified, numbers match company press release exactly, all 8-12 charts embedded, old vs new estimates shown, all hyperlinks clickable, report is 8-12 pages." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Catching errors before delivery maintains professional credibility; institutional clients expect zero factual errors" .

oc:kn_31ec2573 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When executing the full earnings update process" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Follow the 5-phase workflow: (1) Data Collection 30-60min → (2) Analysis 2-3hr → (3) Chart Generation 1-2hr → (4) Report Creation 2-3hr → (5) Quality Check 30min." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sequenced workflow ensures data freshness (Phase 1 first) and quality (Phase 5 last) while managing the 24-48hr turnaround constraint" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_3409a2a7 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing headlines and Page 1 summary" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead with the conclusion: beat or miss? Up or down estimates? Quantify everything — 'strong' means nothing, '$150M beat on $1.2B revenue' is clear." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Institutional readers need the bottom line first; they will read deeper if the conclusion interests them" .

oc:kn_62b9d0b8 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any earnings update report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never rely on training data for earnings figures. Always actively search for and verify the latest earnings release date before proceeding with any analysis." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Training data is always outdated; using stale numbers produces factually incorrect reports that destroy credibility" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_6bbbb1ea a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Throughout the entire report — every number needs a source" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every figure, table, beat/miss analysis, and guidance change must have a specific citation with document name, date, and clickable hyperlink. No plain text URLs allowed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Source attribution is mandatory for institutional compliance and enables clients to verify data independently" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_9e90009c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When identifying the earnings period and quarter labels" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Companies use varying fiscal calendars (e.g., Nike FY ends May, Apple FY ends September, Walmart FY ends January). Identify and account for the company's fiscal year before interpreting quarter labels." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Misinterpreting fiscal vs calendar quarters leads to comparing wrong periods and producing nonsensical YoY/QoQ analysis" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e1822b4b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When updating valuation and price target after earnings" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If estimates changed significantly (>5%), usually change the price target. If thesis strengthened/weakened, may change PT even without estimate change." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Price target should reflect material changes in the investment thesis, not just mechanical estimate updates" .

